|Inferences={{Inference
|Inference.Description=To be functional, a building needs to have structural integrity.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=To be functional, a building needs to be 'upright'
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Some parts of the building (e.g. foundation, pillars) support other parts of the building (e.g., pillars hold up the roof). If a supporting part is damaged, it will not provide as much support, and the building may collapse.
}}{{Inference
